[normal][2007] EWCA 
[normal]Civ
[normal] 266
[normal]Same issue as 
[normal]NASS v Westminster but here it concerned failed asylum seekers so was between s21 and s4.  SSHD intervened on the side of the asylum seekers to argue it should be s21.  Lengthy technical judgment on the statutes and regulations which refers to the ‘elabora
[normal]te paper chase through these interlocking provisions’ and ‘important area of law….in a difficult and sensitive field’
